review_blob: La Trappe tripel is a strong Dutch beer at 8%. Has a little bittersweet taste and does contain hints of coriander. Recommended to try.
Lovely German beer. Very tasty and extremely smooth. Would consider this to be easy to drink alongside many other German brews
Lovely mix of malt barley and hops. Strong too at 7.5%. Easy on the palate and a nice bottled version of the brand. Recommended.
Easy on the palate. Lovely crisp taste. Very nice "hoppy" aroma and taste also.
